short_description: feral feline project is an animal shelter based in wheeling, illinois, united states.
long_description: feral cat spay and neuter program- trap, neuter & return(tnr). our goal is to place cats and kittens in loving and safe homes. if you would like to help feral feline project in its mission to provide needed services, including low-cost spaying & neutering, vaccinations and medical care for feral, stray and adoptable cats, please donate now. in addition to a veterinarian visits, donations go towards building feral cat houses, providing food and needed supplies for foster homes, caretakers and saving the lives of severely injured and sick adoptable kittens and cats. are you passionate about what we're doing. we'll help you find a way to volunteer that best suits you.we are always in desperate need of new foster homes, tnr associates, transporters, vacation coverage, etc. we are a 501 c3, foster home based organization. feral feline project started with two women in the summer of 2007. we have tnr 'd thousands of cats and placed thousands of kittens in furever homes since 2007. we are a team of hard working volunteers that educate, fundraise and help citizens tnr their colonies.

generated_description: feral feline project, legally known as feral feline project inc., is a nonprofit organization based in wheeling, illinois, serving the northern cook county area since 2007. the organization focuses on controlling the feral cat population through trap, neuter, and release (tnr) programs. feral feline project provides low-cost spaying and neutering, vaccinations, and medical care for feral, stray, and adoptable cats. they also operate a small foster home program for adoptable kittens. the organization educates the public and local governments about tnr and aims to improve the acceptance of tnr in the community.
